body:
I'm having the same problem. It looks like the Dockerfile references a website that doesn't exist anymore?

https://github.com/IBM/MAX-Image-Resolution-Enhancer/blob/b1f179c75069451a0c453b8429b9f29ef93069d4/Dockerfile#L19

My web browser says it "can't find the server".

I'm no expert here; I am not sure what the solution is.
Did you find a workaround?

Hey, @Sid-MB 

Instead of using this repo, simply use the model official image from the Dockerhub. You can find the link down here 

[https://developer.ibm.com/exchanges/models/all/max-image-resolution-enhancer/](url)

Hope this can help solve your problem.

> Hey, @Sid-MB 
> 
> 
> 
> Instead of using this repo, simply use the model official image from the Dockerhub. You can find the link down here 
> 
> 
> 
> [https://developer.ibm.com/exchanges/models/all/max-image-resolution-enhancer/](url)
> 
> 
> 
> Hope this can help solve your problem.

That worked, thank you!
That is a dead link not as well.
@sorenwacker weirdly enough, that link in this thread just points to the wrong location, but just putting the url in the browser will lead you to the correct location in the ibm dev docs

@godfather68 that link just redirects here https://github.com/IBM/MAX-Image-Resolution-Enhancer/issues/url

Still not sure how to resolve this issue.

As I said above, you need to just go to the link text URL (and not the embedded one)

https://developer.ibm.com/exchanges/models/all/max-image-resolution-enhancer/

Hello @AlexKalopsia, @godfather68, @vasilzhigilei, 

thank you for your patience, the issue is now fixed: https://github.com/IBM/MAX-Image-Resolution-Enhancer/pull/55

issue.title: Local installation fails. (Windows/Docker)

repository.name: MAX-Image-Resolution-Enhancer
repository.description: Upscale an image by a factor of 4, while generating photo-realistic details.
